here is a json schema for a beta cruiser:

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "beta cruiser",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "name": {"type": "string"},
    "class": {"type": "string"},
    "size": {"type": "integer"},
    "speed": {"type": "number"},
    "armour": {"type": "object", "properties": {
      "hull": {"type": "number"},
      "turret": {"type": "number"}
    }, "required": ["hull", "turret"]},
    "weapons": {"type": "array", "items": {
      "type": "object", "properties": {
        "type": {"type": "string"},
        "calibre": {"type": "integer"},
        "quantity": {"type": "integer"}
      }, "required": ["type", "calibre", "quantity"]
    }},
    "engines": {"type": "array", "items": {
      "type": "object", "properties": {
        "type": {"type": "string"},
        "power": {"type": "number"}
      }, "required": ["type", "power"]
    }},
    "crew": {"type": "object", "properties": {
      "officers": {"type": "integer"},
      "enlisted": {"type": "integer"}
    }, "required": ["officers", "enlisted"]},
    "range": {"type": "object", "properties": {
      "max": {"type": "number"},
      "[fuel capacity]": {"type": "number"}
    }, "required": ["max"]}
  },
  "required": ["name", "class", "size", "speed", "armour", "weapons", "engines", "crew", "range"]
}
```

this schema defines a beta cruiser with the following properties:

- name: a string representing the name of the cruiser
- class: a string representing the class of the cruiser
- size: an integer representing the size of the cruiser
- speed: a number representing the speed of the cruiser
- armour: an object with two properties: hull and turret, both representing the armour values for the cruiser
- weapons: an array of objects, each representing a weapon on the cruiser, with properties type, calibre, and quantity
- engines: an array of objects, each representing an engine on the cruiser, with properties type and power
- crew: an object with two properties: officers and enlisted, both representing the number of crew members
- range: an object with two properties: max and [fuel capacity], both representing the range of the cruiser

the placeholder [fuel capacity] is represented by square brackets, as per your request.
